.TH "SPEECHRECOGNITIONERROREVENT.SPEECHRECOGNITIONERROREVENT" "3JS" "September 30, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent.SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent \-
SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent: SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent() constructor
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent()\f[B]\f[R] constructor
creates a new \f[CR]SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent\f[R] object instance.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
new SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent(type, init)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]type\f[R]
A string containing the name of the event.
This will always be \f[CR]error\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]init\f[R]
An initialization object that contains the following properties:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]error\f[R]
An enumerated value representing the type of error.
See the possible \f[CR]error\f[R] values.
.TP
\f[B]message\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
A string containing more details about the error that was raised.
Note that the specification does not define the exact wording of these
messages \(em implementers must define their own wording.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
You would be unlikely to construct a
\f[CR]SpeechRecognitionErrorEvent\f[R] instance manually.
Such instances are available as event objects inside \f[CR]error\f[R]
event handler functions.
.PP
For example:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] recognition = \f[B]new\f[R] SpeechRecognition();

recognition.addEventListener(\(dqerror\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(\(gaSpeech recognition error detected: ${event.error}\(ga);
  console.log(\(gaAdditional information: ${event.message}\(ga);
});
.EE
